						<summary>

						<p>On the tiers of the entrance to the Saṅgamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Dated Śaka 1140, <hi rend="italic">Phālguṇa,</hi> ba. 3, Tuesday, corresponding to A.D. 1219, March 5.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to refer to some grant made by Polī-raḍi-Surapa-raḍi-Bhīmana for the merit of his mother (Cf. NDI, Part II, Nellore, No. 103).</p>						

						</summary>
